data.current_description: Returns the IAM permissions that the caller has on the specified Access Context Manager resource. The resource can be an AccessPolicy, AccessLevel, or ServicePerimeter. This method does not support other resources.
data.summary_suggestion: Test IAM permissions on Access Context Manager resource
data.description_suggestion: Tests which IAM permissions the authenticated caller has on the specified Access Context Manager resource (AccessPolicy, AccessLevel, or ServicePerimeter). Accepts a TestIamPermissionsRequest containing the resource name and list of permissions to check. Returns a TestIamPermissionsResponse listing only the permissions the caller possesses.
